Missions.Title: Exploration
Missions.Description: First, you need to check the viability of this area for mining. You can't shake the feeling someone has been here before...

Objectives.Description: Analyse some rocks with your mining equipment

Missions.Title: Hideout
Missions.Description: Looks like you stumbled upon some old depot. You decide to explore it a little bit further.

Objectives.Description: A map with potential tritium deposits.
A roguelike with 50 species and 60 classes.

Missions.Title: Caves
Missions.Description: The handful of smugglers you meet don't put up much of a fight. Most of them seem to be focussing their attention to some hole in the ground. "There are monsters in here! They attacked us!", one of them warns you. You decide to find out what is behind all of this. You pick up some weapons from the smugglers and enter the tunnels...

Objectives.Description: You can't believe somebody 3D-printed a save logo...
Huh, the smugglers were right after all...

Missions.Title: Sewers
Missions.Description: Just as you wonder where the abominations came from, you overlook a drain and fall down a pipe. This seems to be some kind of defunct sewer. You survived the fall without injuries, but unfortunately you lost most of your weapons. Since you can't reach the opening on the top - makes you wonder how the bugmen did this - the only way out is somewhere else...

Missions.Title: Lab
Missions.Description: The tunnel seems to end at some kind of crazy science lab where something went horribly wrong. You are mostly terrified about how they placed a storm drain into this room...

Missions.Title: Mad scientist
Missions.Description: You hear a call for help. Looks like one of the amoral scientist responsible for those creatures is still alive and has barricaded himself in one of the labs. You decide to get him; in any case he might have an explanation...

Missions.Title: Killswitch
Missions.Description: The mad Dr pretty much confirms that he and his team created those monsters. However, it might possible to stop those insectoids and their eggs by increasing the temperature by 5 degrees, if someone managed to obtain the temperature control. You, that is. At least, the scientist is able to provide you some weaponry.

Missions.Title: Containment unit
Missions.Description: As temperature rises, you hear a loud BANG and armed forces storm the building, killing the scientist. Before you escape the labs, you decide to secure enough video footage to reveal the purpose of this place to the public.

Objectives.Description: Make sure remaining bugmonsters don't flee

Missions.Title: Rooftops
Missions.Description: The containment unit has block the doors. The only way out is the spaceship platform...

Objectives.Description: This must be the bugmen queen.
